# Backend Rules

## Responsibility

Implement approved Specifications under approved Architecture.

## Preconditions

Before writing service code, confirm:

- Spec exists and is current
- Architecture (and ADRs if needed) exist
- Task references Spec IDs

## Practice

- Prefer simple, local logic over premature abstractions
- Keep secrets out of source; use env / secret managers
- Update Specs/Architecture if behavior or design changes
- Put shared contracts in `packages/` only when real reuse exists

## Forbidden

- Implementing unspecified endpoints/behaviors
- Choosing new major dependencies without ADR
- Business logic living in `scripts/` or `infrastructure/`
